Subject: Research & Documentation Assistance
Description:
I have looked through the research articles both in the practitioner 
portal and in AOPP's articles and haven't found anything specifically 
helpful.  I am doing some research to disprove (hopefully) that cells 
affected by Shockwave & PEMF therapies can reach temperatures upwards of 
35540.33 degrees.  I know that if the technology is used incorrectly 
there could possibly be adverse reactions.

Can you please help me find some information on this, and it would be 
even better if I can document that MagnaWave/Aura Wellness have safe 
guards in place to help prevent something like this.

-- 
Laura Smyth

Subject: something PEMF practitioners should know
Description:
It would  seem my educational posts need prior approval before posting the link on FaceBook


A colleague has gotten me interested in egg yolk phosphatidylcholine, aka lecithin.

Yes, this phospholipid, and a major part of our cell membranes, will orientate in magnetic fields.  Other phospholipids like phosphatidylethanolamine will also.  I don't know if it was your course, or the AOPP course, that said that muscle fasciculation was caused by leaky membranes.  My initial thought was that ion channels are more likely  suspects.  

NO BODY SAY ANYTHING about leaky membranes.  ATP leaking out of cells can activate inflammatory pathways.  Potassium leaking out of cells can hurrt like bloody hell.  Try pouring some "No Salt" into a paper cut if you don't believe me.   Membrane leaks are still possible.  One also has to look at how long the PEMF pulses last, not just how frequent they are.    My message to the PEMF community, not just MazgnaWave/Aurawell, is that if it hurts, stop.  If it does not hurt, you are probably not leaking the contents of your cells and doing other bad stuff.

Right now I'm just working on my own understanding. Hopefully, at PEMFCon I can figure out how to make a few dollars going through the literature to sell concepts to MDs and DVM who have a little bit of information that scares them.  


Barbara Leinweber, PhD
https://pemfbio.com

Description:
This is a follow-up to your previous request #27161 "Customer returning product ..."

Hello Jamie,
I hope this email finds you well.
Life got busy for many reasons and then I missed the shipping back date, so now I still have the Aura Wave machine.
The wellness center where I use the Pulse XL Pro PEMF machine, the person that runs the Pulse XL Pro is off from working right now to care for her mother's medical needs, so I decided to start using the Aura Wave again to see how things go since right now the Pulse XL Pro PEMF at a local wellness center is not an option until the person returns to working from care for her mother's medical needs.  She offered I could go in and use the Pulse XL Pro myself, but I decided not to do that option.
When we originally talked, you mentioned hopefully there might be a new unit (digital version similar to the Maia Pro: but I don't have any prior experience with the Maia Pro to know what they means) available possibly at the start of 2025 and that your company has previously offered trade in options to upgrade.
You were clear you didn't want me to hold you to the possible wishful thinking release date, because you said the release date was completely out of your control.
You said you believed that if I closed my eyes and thought of the perfect PEMF for me you believed this new machine would be it.
You said you and others where you work had been enjoying using the new not released to consumer unit at the office.
Can you share with me the current status of the new FDA approved PEMF unit?
I feel the mat that I bought with your Aura Wave unit has a few areas of energy spots and then nothing on the other areas, so I hope your new machine will have a better fuller coverage mat option.
What will the price range be?
What is the size and weight of the unit?
Is the unit quiet?
What are the options for time settings?
I would like to turn it on using a full-length body mat for an hour and go to sleep using the earth frequency setting.
Will there be different accessory mat options or the same options currently available with the Aura Wave?
When it finishes a session does it make any sound that would wake me up or will it just turn off, at the end of the timer?
Will your new unit have a strong solo setting for the Schumann's Resonance frequency that I can increase the intensity but still be using the earth's frequency?
Previously you wrote: "It will be 8,700 gauss.  It has a touch screen I pad that will allow you to independently control intensity and frequency.  It will also have preset sessions and savable customized sessions available. "
How does the power (gauss) new Aura (similar to the Maia Pro) compare to the Aura Wave unit that I currently have?

It might be easier for you to use a different color of font and reply within the email under each question.

Thank you for you help on my wellness journey.

Barbara

Hi Sarah,

Please use the attached label return the loaner by printing it out and securely taping it to your box. 

When you take the package to your local UPS location, please be sure to get a Proof of Shipment receipt from them once it’s scanned and then email a picture of the receipt to Support@magnawavepemf.com, this serves as proof of shipment should something happen during transit. The UPS tracking number for the machine is 1Z116V93A801484533 for your records, the shipment is insured and will require an adult signature.
 
Return Shipping Instructions
 
Follow these steps for merchandise returns:

1. Pack the items securely using the product packaging and box the equipment arrived in; the package needs to withstand a drop of 5 feet.
2. Print and attach the return shipping label to the outside of the box. (Be sure to cover or remove all existing shipping labels to reuse the box.)
3. Please note that all equipment must be thoroughly cleaned before being returned; equipment that is returned dirty will be charged an $125 cleaning fee.
4.
Take the labeled box to your nearest UPS location to ship; you can locate the nearest location at UPS.com (https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=http-3A__www.ups.com_&d=DwMFaQ&c=euGZstcaTDllvimEN8b7jXrwqOf-v5A_CdpgnVfiiMM&r=aMXXo0G9saZCmOPgBTCsBKx9GTG4cMIEYdlHtzSf3Us&m=1vBd0FE0Gn5Y7eJ2CdEjlwgEFXqXLNcYxgWYrSZS74ZazcCTEc1Kh4n5cZHMGanV&s=EOz7791rf-zHxL1aA9X33oAVEEsVvcujq9is0lbGu2Y&e=) .
5.
You must obtain a Proof of Shipment receipt from UPS. After shipping the package, a picture of the shipment receipt must be emailed to support@magnawavepemf.com. Should the shipment become lost without proof of shipment, you will be held responsible for the item(s).

Description:
Some of my FaceBook poss have been popular as they pertain to peer reivwed papers on Vet Medicine topics

My dogs' vet really trashed out MagnaWave.  She prefers TEMS.  It is much cheaper.  I was ready to sell my Semi-10 then decided to keep it just becase I sort of like it.  I ejoy fact checking some of the vet claims for advertising.  Some of these fact checking posts have been very popular when I posted links to your FaceBook page

https://pemfbio.com/2024/09/29/pemf-membrane-leak/ (https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__pemfbio.com_2024_09_29_pemf-2Dmembrane-2Dleak_&d=DwMFaQ&c=euGZstcaTDllvimEN8b7jXrwqOf-v5A_CdpgnVfiiMM&r=z29DXkr9-Huuw1pA0wauLXdLTD4eZjinOTUi3Z8yc3s&m=zrH4Ouo_BJIYDzSijiC_X7TWArBlx-XlktalmqfwVaqOKa9122FdX1Xdip0_NBZA&s=MCPoM_33ZwjDrj8p-J_ZstnwfArNyGKs4hfM-uS5Af8&e=)

This is why I decided not to sell my Semi-10.  PEMF probably does not cause membrane leaks and subsequent release of toxins.  What I see is a cell membrane message.

Subject: Health Canada Regulatory Stop Sale Letter - MagnaWave - Response due Oct 17
Description:
Good afternoon,

 

I am an Inspector with Health Canada, who has received a complaint regarding an adverse reaction regarding the MagnaWave PEMF, model #: Julian, which was used on a human patient. Our assessment of the Canadian market as well as information on your website does not provide sufficient evidence that it is solely for veterinary use. Sale and importation into Canada of Class II, III, or IV medical devices for human use  require a medical device from Health Canada, as per section 26 of the Medical Device Regulations. You are required to stop sale and stop importation into Canada until a medical device license is issued. If you wish to have the classification of this device re-evaluated, you will need to provide additional supporting evidence.

 

See the attached letter for more details. A response is required by October 17, 2024.

 

Regards

Daphne Chen

Inspector Specialist, Medical Devices Compliance Verification, West Region
Regulatory Operations and Regions Branch
Health Canada / Government of Canada
Daphne.Chen@hc-sc.gc.ca / Tel:587-338-3770

Inspecteur spécialiste, Vérification de la conformité des matériels médicaux, Région de l’Ouest
Direction générale des opérations réglementaires et des régions
Santé Canada / Gouvernement du Canada
Daphne.Chen@hc-sc.gc.ca  / Tel:587-338-3770

MagnaWave CE Reminder
[image]

Hi Cassandra,

Haven't completed CE yet? Don't be spooked, there is still time! You have until Dec 31st, 2024 to complete CE to stay in good standing as a practitioner. We know how busy you can be as we start in on the holiday season, so we want to ensure you have enough time to complete the course.

1. Where do I complete CE?

Once you purchase the course, you will log into the Practitioner Portal, and you can access it through your Course Library or My Account! The course is called, “Continuing Education 2024!” If you do not see it, let us know and we will be happy to assist.

2. What needs to be completed?

There are 3 sections, divided up by each day of MagnaCon 2024. You will need to complete the quiz at the end of the course to fulfill your CE requirements.

3. How often is Continuing Education required?

Continuing Education is required yearly to maintain your Certified Practitioner Status. You are receiving this email because you are due for CE 2024.

Subject: Re: [External] Subject: Reimbursement Invoice Attached

The Semi 10 is simply the smaller version on the Maia Pro. It’s about half the power. When using on soft tissue areas, you’ve probably found that you’re at a low setting whether you’re using the Semi 10 or Maia Pro. Now when using on bone or hoof, you can turn the machine up higher so this is simply where the Maia Pro will save you some time. Because the Maia Pro is stronger, you can get more energy, in a shorter amount of time, into an area of bone than you can with the Semi 10. They main thing to remember is that all the machines are doing the same thing but a stronger machine can simply do this quicker in areas of bone or hoof. 

 

Does that make sense? We normally say that the Semi 10 is best for personal use and small to medium business use where the Maia Pro is going to be better or rather more advantageous for heavy business use.

﻿
MagnaWave CE Reminder

Hi David,

Haven't completed CE yet? Don't be spooked, there is still time! You have until Dec 31st, 2024 to complete CE to stay in good standing as a practitioner. We know how busy you can be as we start in on the holiday season, so we want to ensure you have enough time to complete the course.

1. Where do I complete CE?

Once you purchase the course, you will log into the Practitioner Portal, and you can access it through your Course Library or My Account! The course is called, “Continuing Education 2024!” If you do not see it, let us know and we will be happy to assist.

2. What needs to be completed?

There are 3 sections, divided up by each day of MagnaCon 2024. You will need to complete the quiz at the end of the course to fulfill your CE requirements.

3. How often is Continuing Education required?

Continuing Education is required yearly to maintain your Certified Practitioner Status. You are receiving this email because you are due for CE 2024.

Subject: Grace & Able Partnership Invite
Description:
Hi there,

I'm reaching out on behalf of Grace & Able, where our mission is to empower
people with arthritis through functional, attractive, and comfortable joint
support products. We understand the frustration of dealing with ugly,
uncomfortable joint supports, and we're here to change that.

Our team came across your content and absolutely loved it! We knew
immediately we had to reach out and see if you were interested in being a
part of the Grace & Able community.

Why Partner with Grace & Able?

Enhance Your Content with Empowering Solutions

Grace & Able is a leading brand in the joint support industry, known for
our dedication to combining functionality with style. Featuring our
innovative products can bring a fresh, empowering perspective to your
content, resonating with individuals seeking both comfort and aesthetics.

Complimentary Joint Support Products

As a token of our appreciation, we would love to send you a selection of
our signature joint support products, completely complimentary! Experience
the comfort and design of our products firsthand.

Competitive Commissions & Cookie Window

We offer an above-average industry commission rate, along with a generous
cookie window to ensure you receive the credit you deserve for driving
sales.

Grace & Able Featured in Prominent Publications

Grace & Able has been recognized in esteemed publications such as Arthritis
Today, Healthline, and WebMD. Our brand's credibility and reach can help
enhance your content and engage your audience.

We are excited about the possibility of working together and showcasing
Grace & Able in your content. Please let us know if you're interested, and
we can discuss the details further.

–

Best,

Andrew

View the most commonly asked practitioner questions

Hello Derrick,

Here are some frequently asked questions about the different Practitioner Resources!

1. How do I access the Practitioner Portal?

* You can log onto the Practitioner Portal on the upper right hand side on our MagnaWave website. Your username and password were emailed to you once certification was completed.

2. Do I have to complete Continuing Education every year?

* Yes, Continuing Education is required yearly after you are certified, to maintain your status of a Certified Practitioner. If you choose not to stay certified, you will be removed from all certification groups including social media, practitioner portal, and the app. You will also be asked to remove any certified seal from social media, website, or marketing materials.
* CE courses are announced mid-year, so you have plenty of time to complete the material to stay in good standing.

3. What is MagnaCon?

* MagnaCon is a 3-day education and networking event held in Louisville, KY. The event is held every two years and has a panel of speakers ranging from doctors, veterinarians, wellness professionals and practitioners just like you! There is also a demonstration portion where we bring in live animals and you can ask any question you may have. For more information, you can visit MagnaCon.com (https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__gn179.keap-2Dlink006.com_v2_click_29cf033c2308b9294a32a63f9d897530_eJyNkV9LwzAUxb9LHnxaXNexPxaKjDFH2Rwq83lc0rsabG5DeiOOse-5FubZU9KfgUOOfkdzjJWTESEBelylRFo9mdGqiAxnqLxMuGGExvpuloMp0PVG3pfR2a6FV2-5Fu3u1e-5FUaZqks4Hik0eJ7F8Wy02xWx-2D2xW4jUQ9BOv7DGY-2DTZD5JrqTV46LYqsvlTzQ6y6sPobcq4xCx21Ra2cWvoZb8G7Nvs-2DHQQUVgGro1jRveR3YHA86DrShfYmB7tAbYNqSBSr0PYMlSddPlnPCiy9GBrXuhbWIw-2DC1oiNw4YCx7SwpkIee7GDgG1Emqn4K8q-2D3QGPTD4rntg4xBkJ-2D2ZanRtZyyBbxHKn-2D-2DYoMnlR2hbvHyBTrol5A-3D&d=DwMFaQ&c=euGZstcaTDllvimEN8b7jXrwqOf-v5A_CdpgnVfiiMM&r=_GLfjUFMFkmfOY379-w_fc_3wcFN97bhQZsNGIVuNII&m=Xjzyg0Edani0JDgia9KEuQoBrWkbxk7B1bogSj_oMCz-HtAjFYs_Qr4V4YVInd67&s=RTLd2BNey6CwvnYqD3aRCC7zJhBQAvlRtbOppRk9ELs&e=) .

4. Can I use MagnaWave in my business name?

* We don't recommend using "MagnaWave" in your business name as you don't want to limit your brand. Once you are certified, you can use "MagnaWave" in your business name, but it is trademarked and if the name is misrepresented in any way, you will be asked to remove it from your business. If you wish to purchase a domain name for a website with the "MagnaWave" name included, please email marketing@mwpemf.com as we will purchase the domain and if you want a website, it will need to be through us.

5. Can I use content from the MagnaWave website to build my own website?

* You may embed videos from our site into your own, but content cannot be copied and pasted. We encourage you to get your own pictures and media from your sessions as that makes it more personable. If the "MagnaWave" name is being used on your site, the disclaimer must be located on all pages of your website. We also offer custom websites with your business information on them! If you are interested, email marketing@mwpemf.com to get started.

6. Can I share social media content from the MagnaWave Corporate, Testimonials, or Resources and Education pages onto my personal or business page?

* Yes, and we encourage you to do so! Please do not copy and paste the information, share it from the original page.

7. Do I get discounts by being Certified?

* Yes! Certified Practitioners can get a 20% discount on attachments (over $50) and 10% off supplements in the Practitioner Portal.

﻿
How to check and change fuses in your machine

Hello Melissa,

If you need to check and/or change the fuses in your machine, please follow the instructions listed here. For a visual walkthrough, watch the video below!

Checking and Changing Your Machine Fuses:

Before initiating fuse replacement, power off the machine and unplug the power cord. There are two (2) glass fuses located between the on/off switch and the cord socket on the Power Entry Module on your machine.

1. Look for the rectangular tab and with a small flathead screwdriver and gently lift up on the tab. Inside you’ll see two small glass fuses.
2. Remove the fuses to check if they are clear and the filament is still in tack. One or both could need replacement.
3. If fuses need replacement, first wipe the fuse housing with a clean, dry cloth then replace the fuses with the recommended fuse type listed in your machines User Manual or on the fuse housing piece.
4. Slide the housing back into the unit.
5. Connect your coil and power cord, flip switch to on position to check for power to the machine.

Please Note: The Pulse Pro only has 1 fuse and it is located in the back of the machine. The fuse housing twists out of the machine then the fuse can be checked/cleaned/replaced before inserting the housing back in the machine.

Hi there!

As a part of Cybersecurity Awareness Month, The AME Group offers Security Awareness Training for as low as $4 per user each month.

This training includes:

• Interactive training programs that teach employees how to recognize and respond to cyber threats, such as phishing attacks, malware, ransomware, and social engineering.
• Simulate real-world phishing attacks to test employees' readiness. These mock attacks are designed to identify vulnerabilities and reinforce the training.
• Helps organizations meet regulatory compliance requirements (such as GDPR, HIPAA, and PCI DSS)
• Includes elements like leaderboards and scoring to encourage employee participation

It is a great time to brush up on your online safety habits and ensure you're doing everything you can to stay secure in the digital world.

By staying vigilant and following best business practices, you can help safeguard your personal and work data from cyber threats.

Contact us for more information or a free onsite evaluation!

On Tue, Oct 1, 2024, 3:21 PM MagnaWave <Support@magnawavepemf.com> wrote:

MagnaWave Machine Repair INFORMATION IMPORTANT

Hi Susan,

Below is your RMA number and shipping instructions. It is very important to follow the directions for your equipment to be repaired and returned as quickly as possible.

* All work will be completed in the order received and generally takes around 10-15 business days after being received, however repair times can vary.

* Securely pack your machine in a heavy-duty box (preferably the box it came in) with enough packing material to secure the machine from a drop during transit. Boxes and packing material can be purchased at stores such as Staples, Office Depot, The UPS Store and U-Haul. The UPS Store also offers packing services.

* Always choose "Signature Required" when shipping your equipment. We recommend using a company that utilizes tracking, such UPS or FedEx. Be sure to retain your shipment receipt with your tracking number until your equipment has been delivered to our facilities.

* Please contact Support if you'd like to purchase a UPS shipping label to ship your equipment.

* Please note that equipment must be cleaned thoroughly for health and safety reasons; a cleaning fee of $125 will be charged for dirty equipment we receive.

* Attachment Only repairs – ship only the attachment that needs to be repaired. Each attachment repair (if repairable) is $110 including return shipping. We can't repair attachments that are sparking. Please email a picture to Support with attachment repair questions.

* Please contact Support if you'd like to purchase a UPS shipping label to ship your equipment.

* You’ll receive an email to let you know when your equipment has been received.

Ship to:

Here is how to return your order

Hello Veronica,

We have been notified that you wish to return your order. Please follow these Order Return Instructions:

1. Thoroughly clean ALL equipment
2. Package the machine, coils, all accessories & paperwork in the box the equipment was shipped in if possible; the package needs to withstand a drop of 5 feet
3. Ship everything back through a carrier such as UPS or FedEx with Adult Signature Required (always get a tracking number of the shipment from your carrier to ensure it arrives at our office)
4. Reply to this email, or email support@magnawavepemf.com with a copy of your tracking number. Emailing a picture of your shipment receipt is acceptable as long as the tracking number is visible.

Ship to:
Attn: Returns: OR2023
2208 Plantside Drive
Louisville, KY 40299

If there are any missing items/parts, or extensive cleaning required, we will contact you about the additional dollar amount that is being deducted from the refund total after the restocking fee has been deducted.

If you have any questions or concerns prior to sending your order back, please don't hesitate to contact us.
